    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SINGLE REDUCTION, SINGLE DRIVE AXLES: EATON - LUBRICATION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl1401215">
        <title>LUBRICATION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Proper lubrication is vital for optimal drive axle service life. Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in
                the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for recommended lube, change intervals, and quantity.
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="lubricate" graphiccount="0">
            <title>LUBE LEVEL</title>
            <para>The proper lubricant fill level is even with the bottom of the filler hole. A level close enough to be
                seen or touched is not enough. Lube must be even with the bottom of the filler hole.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Check and clean housing breather vent at each lube level check.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
